{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "f3a9c1e2-7b4d-4e8a-9c2f-ivory-mini-feed",
    "name": "Ivory Mini Feed API",
    "description": "Collection per testare la Mini Feed API del test tecnico Ivory.\n\n**Come usarla:**\n1. Avvia il backend (`cd backend && npm run dev` — porta 3000).\n2. Esegui prima **Auth → Login (solo email)**: il token viene salvato automaticamente nella variabile `accessToken` e usato da tutte le richieste protette.\n3. **Post → Crea post** salva automaticamente `postId`; **Commenti → Crea commento** salva `commentId`. Così puoi eseguire le richieste in sequenza senza copiare ID a mano.\n\n**Utenti seed:** `ada@ivory.test` (admin) e `alan@ivory.test` (user) — password `ivory1234` (opzionale: il login funziona anche solo con l'email).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "adminToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "postId", "value": "post-1" },
    { "key": "commentId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "cursor", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["health"] },
            "description": "Verifica che il server sia attivo. Non richiede autenticazione."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (solo email — mock)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"ada@ivory.test\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["v1", "auth", "login"] },
            "description": "Login mock come da spec: basta l'email, la password è opzionale. Salva automaticamente `accessToken` e `adminToken` (Ada è admin)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Ritorna accessToken', () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property('accessToken'));",
                  "pm.test('Ritorna user senza password', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json).to.have.property('user');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.user).to.not.have.property('password');",
                  "});",
                  "if (json.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.accessToken);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('adminToken', json.accessToken);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (con password)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"alan@ivory.test\",\n  \"password\": \"ivory1234\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["v1", "auth", "login"] },
            "description": "Se la password viene inviata, deve essere corretta. Salva `accessToken` (Alan è user normale)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "if (json.accessToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.accessToken);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login con password errata → 401",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"ada@ivory.test\",\n  \"password\": \"sbagliata\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["v1", "auth", "login"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
                  "pm.test('Errore in formato { error }', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('error'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login con email inesistente → 401",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"nessuno@ivory.test\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["v1", "auth", "login"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Feed",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Feed — prima pagina (limit=3)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/feed?limit=3",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "feed"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "3" }]
            },
            "description": "Feed pubblica paginata. Salva `nextCursor` nella variabile `cursor` per la richiesta successiva."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Ritorna 3 post', () => pm.expect(json.posts).to.have.lengthOf(3));",
                  "pm.test('Ogni post ha likedByMe, likesCount, commentsCount, author', () => {",
                  "  const p = json.posts[0];",
                  "  pm.expect(p).to.have.property('likedByMe');",
                  "  pm.expect(p).to.have.property('likesCount');",
                  "  pm.expect(p).to.have.property('commentsCount');",
                  "  pm.expect(p).to.have.property('author');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Author non espone la password', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.posts[0].author).to.not.have.property('password');",
                  "});",
                  "if (json.nextCursor) pm.collectionVariables.set('cursor', json.nextCursor);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Feed — pagina successiva (cursor)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/feed?limit=3&cursor={{cursor}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "feed"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "limit", "value": "3" },
                { "key": "cursor", "value": "{{cursor}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Esegui prima «Feed — prima pagina» per popolare la variabile `cursor`."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('nextCursor presente (o null se ultima pagina)', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('nextCursor');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Feed — limit oltre il massimo (50 → max 20)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/feed?limit=50",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "feed"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "50" }]
            },
            "description": "Il limite viene comunque ridotto a 20."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Massimo 20 post', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().posts.length).to.be.at.most(20));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Feed — autenticata (likedByMe personalizzato)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/feed?limit=5",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "feed"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "5" }]
            },
            "description": "Con il token, `likedByMe` riflette i like dell'utente autenticato."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
